long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1222039 build.log
Description of problem: Package castor fails to build from source in Fedora Rawhide.
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable): 1.3.3-3.fc24
Steps to Reproduce: koji build --scratch f26 castor-1.3.3-3.fc24.src.rpm
Additional info: This package is tracked by Koschei. See: http://apps.fedoraproject.org/koschei/package/castor
*** Bug 1403021 has been marked as a duplicate of this bug. ***
I'd just like to point out that bug #1403021 (closed as a duplicate of this one) provided a patch to fix the build failure.

Add as BuildRequires maven-source-plugin is really useless. This plugin should be added in the BRs list when is really necessary (see byteman) to avoid waste on time and resources on some "slow - crappy" arches (e.g. arm*) Use "%pom_remove_plugin -r :maven-source-plugin" next time we dont need "sources" artifacts
